description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton Hospital or Harefield Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sleep and Ventilation Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Respiratory Clinical Physiologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Jobs Ref: 312-RB-0344-A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 year - Maternity cover&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 Available positions &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is the largest heart and lung centre in the UK and among the largest in Europe. We are a partnership of two specialist hospitals which are known throughout the world for our expertise, standard of care and research success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play an active role working in this busy and prestigious department and will be involved with setting up and analysis of sleep studies with a particular emphasis on full polysomnographic studies including sleep scoring and staging. You will also set up patients on non-invasive ventilators (NIV) and also CPAP and be involved in troubleshooting any on-going problems. You will provide a ventilator data download service to aid optimization of ventilator settings and assist in the CPAP AirView reporting service for the department, with consultant supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to work closely with all the consultants and other clinical physiologists in the department including members of the multi-disciplinary team. It is essential that you are self-motivated and have good communication skills. You should hold a BSc degree (or equivalent qualification) and registration with the appropriate governing body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note that this role is not exclusive to physiologists. Allied Health Professionals and registered nurses with a suitable background are encouraged to apply.&lt;/strong&gt; The department has a long history of multi-disciplinary staffing with supportive training in place to develop successful candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you require any further information regarding this post please contact Vitor Roldao or Anna Hanak via email on v.roldao@rbht.nhs.uk or a.hanak@rbht.nhs.uk or telephone on 0207 352 8121 ext. 4206&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 20 November 20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Due to the popularity of some positions, we reserve the right to close the vacancies early on receipt of sufficient applicants. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You are providing your personal information to the Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust for the purposes of staff administration; administration of membership records (Foundation Trust Membership); crime prevention &amp; prosecution of offenders; National Fraud initiative and occupational health purposes and by applying for this post you hereby consent to the Trust processing of your personal data as outlined above. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
